** About the Team **

ASD is entering an exciting phase of growth, innovation and transformation.
Our agency has committed to delivering REDSPICE, which is the most significant
single investment in the Australian Signals Directorate’s 75 years.

  

The Operational Engineering (OE) Branch comprises high-performing, dynamic,
multidisciplinary teams committed to enabling ASD’s missions in unique and
exciting ways. Our people are highly skilled and work at the forefront of
innovation to support mission requirements through their specialist skills in
software, firmware and/or electronic development.

  

** The Role **

Python developers are accountable for the design, delivery and maintenance of
a range of microservices, web-applications and data processing workflows to
support capability development and operations.

  

OE Branch are looking for individuals who:

  * Enjoy working as members of an integrated, agile team; 
  * Look for innovative ways to solve problems, streamline processes and improve procedures; 
  * Will help design, deliver and maintain python-backed applications, micro-services and data processing pipelines; 
  * Are interested in learning new technologies, languages and development methodologies; 
  * Drive concepts and build them into workable and appropriate solutions for mission outcomes; 
  * Demonstrate dynamic analytical thinking, resilience, and adaptability. 

_ If you are successful in the application and assessment process, you will be
placed into a merit pool and may be contacted for further testing as positions
become available. These may be ongoing or non-ongoing opportunities. _

_ _

_ Throughout the year, ASD may contact you to reconfirm your interest in roles
and update you with any relevant information. We request that you also let us
know if your circumstances change and you no longer wish to remain in the
merit pool. _

** Our Ideal Candidate **

The occupants of these positions play a pivotal role in the design,
development and delivery of critical capabilities used by ASD’s workforce,
ensuring they are fit-for-purpose to meet sensitive and time-critical mission
requirements.

  

Interested candidates should have contemporary qualifications and/or
demonstrated skills and experience in one or more of the following areas:

  * Python programming 
  * Contemporary web development frameworks such as React 
  * Microservice architectures and API integration 
  * Containerised software development 
  * Orchestration services including Ansible, Puppet, Satelitte and/or Terraform 
  * CI/CD tooling and automation including Artifactory, BitBucket, GitLab and Jenkins 
  * Messaging and dataflow services such as RabbitMQ, Kafka and/or NiFi 
  * Strong understanding of the role and function of each layer of the OSI model 
  * Experience developing and testing critical software, and integrating with complex systems 

